{
  "texts": [
    "It is a well-known empirical fact that Lagrangian velocity increments develop scaling power laws in the inertial range, τ η ≪ τ ≪ τ L, as measured by the Lagrangian structure functions 33, 54, 55 of order p:",
    "where with 〈 ⋅ 〉, we indicate an average over all N p trajectories and over time.",
    "For both DNS and DM-3c,",
    "τ is calculated by further averaging over all velocity components.",
    "Henceforth, we neglect the dependence on the velocity component because of isotropy."
  ]
}